<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crimea Debate Continues on Council Deputy Status </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crimea Debate Continues on Council Deputy Status </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406171994 Kiev UT-1 Television Network in Ukrainian 1600 
GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406171994 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UT-1 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Crimean parliament continued today the debate on 
the status of the Crimean Supreme Council deputy. Members voted 
against the amendment requiring them to be guided in their work 
not only by the law, but by their conscience. They also 
rejected the amendment requiring them to take an oath of loyalty 
to the people of Crimea. However, the majority voted to allow 
deputies to carry personal weapons. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

