<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Faction Protests Russian Move Into Conflict Zone </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Faction Protests Russian Move Into Conflict Zone </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406201894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1759 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1406201894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian United Republican Party parliamentary 
faction has categorically protested the introduction of the 
Russian parachute regiment stationed in Gudauta (Abkhazia) to 
the zone of the Georgian-Abkhazian conflict. 
  The faction, which includes 21 deputies, circulated a 
statement saying that this very regiment was fighting against 
the Georgian Armed Forces in Abkhazia and was the first to come 
to Sukhumi. 
  Deputy Jaba Ioseliani said in parliament today that under a 
special Russian-Georgian agreement the Gudauta regiment would 
not be brought to the security zone on the Inguri River. 
  Ioseliani intended to meet Russian First Deputy Defense 
Minister Georgiy Kondratyev on June 15 in order to discuss the 
details of implementation of the peacekeeping operation in the 
conflict zone. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

