<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Shevardnadze Meets With World Bank Officials </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shevardnadze Meets With World Bank Officials </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1406200094 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1327 GMT 14 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1406200094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] [No dateline as received] -- Yesterday, 13 June, 
Georgian Head of State Eduard Shevardnadze received a World Bank 
delegation led by the head of the bank's Europe and Central Asia 
department, Mr. Blinkhorn. 
  The Georgian leader briefed guests on the current situation 
in the republic, stressing that as a result of reforms that had 
been implemented recently signs of stabilization were emerging 
in the country. Shevardnadze said that a fast pace of 
privatization would create a real basis for the development of 
business. 
  For their part, World Bank representatives said that their 
program envisaged rendering aid to Georgia in the near future, 
particularly for the winter season. The program also envisaged 
investment in the republic and the provision of technical 
assistance initially to Tbilisi, Poti, and Batumi, and later to 
other regions. 
  The head of state thanked delegation members for their 
interest in Georgia and assured them of all-round assistance 
from the republic's government. 

</TEXT>

