<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   UN Observers Arrive in Sukhumi 15 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UN Observers Arrive in Sukhumi 15 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506101794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0929 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506101794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Irina Shchegoleva] </F>
  [Text] Sochi June 15 TASS -- Four U.N. military observers 
arrived in Sukhumi on Wednesday to monitor a CIS peace-keeping 
operation in Abkhazia, a spokesman in the Abkhazian Ministry of 
Information and the Press, told ITAR-TASS. 
  According to the same source, a total of 88 U.N. observers 
are to be posted in the area of the deployment of a CIS 
peace-keeping force along Inguri river. 
  General supervision will be exercised by Colonel-General 
Georgiy Kondratyev, Russian deputy defence minister, from the 
Russian peace- keeping force headquarters in Sukhumi. 

</TEXT>

