<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Calls IAEA Resolution `Start of Sanctions' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Calls IAEA Resolution `Start of Sanctions' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1606111894 Moscow Radio Moscow in Korean 1100 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1606111894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radio Moscow </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Son Song-pil, DPRK ambassador in Moscow, has said 
that the Korean [choson] Government withdrew from the 
International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] because this agency's 
Board of Governors had recently adopted a resolution on the 
North Korean issue. 
  During a news conference, Ambassador Son Song-pil stressed 
that the IAEA Board of Governors' adoption of the resolution 
meant, in reality, the start of sanctions against the DPRK. 
  Ambassador Son Song-pil also declared that imposing 
sanctions 
against Pyongyang and convening an international conference on 
the denuclearization of the Korean peninsula were in no way 
compatible. 

</TEXT>

