<H3> <TI>   No Signing 16 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    No Signing 16 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606094694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0845 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606094694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Andrey Kirillov and </F>
Andrey Bychkov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 16 Jun [TASS] -- The treaty on the basis of 
friendly relations between the Russian Federation and the SRV, 
which had been prepared for signing by the Russian and 
Vietnamese governments, will not be signed today, an ITAR-TASS 
correspondent has been told by circles close to the Russian 
Government. 
  According to sources close to the Vietnamese delegation, the 
questions of the United Nations' role in the world and Vietnam's 
debt to Russia, following its succession from the former USSR, 
still need to be agreed upon. 
  According to Vietnamese sources, questions of the 
prospecting 
and joint extraction of oil and gas by the "Vetsovpetro" 
enterprise and problems of the Vietnamese community in Russia 
also remain unsolved. Nor has agreement been reached on the 
question of the base at Cam Ranh, as Vietnam has put forward a 
proposal to review the conditions of its lease. 

</TEXT>

