<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Cites `Landmark' Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cites `Landmark' Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506192894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1915 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506192894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Andrey Kirillov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 15 TASS -- Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo 
Van Kiet's current visit to Moscow is a landmark in the 
development of Russian-Vietnamese relations, Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev said on Wednesday. 
  Kozyrev met with his Vietnamese counterpart Nguyen Manh Cam 
who is accompanying Vo Van Kiet on his visit to Russia. 
  Kozyrev stressed that Russia "builds relations with its old 
friends on a new basis." He noted that Russia and Vietnam have 
big mutual interests, including in the political sphere. He 
described relations between the two countries as "very concrete, 
good, strong and friendly." 
  Nguyen Manh Cam pointed out that Vietnam pays much attention 
to the strengthening of relations with the countries with which 
it has traditional ties, primarily Russia. "We value our 
friendship very much," he said. 

</TEXT>

