Daily Report 
<DATE1>  15 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Comments on DPRK Sanctions </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Comments on DPRK Sanctions </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506172694 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1645 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506172694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Andrey Kirillov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 15 Jun -- If the world community introduced 
sanctions against North Korea this would be an extremely 
unfavorable turn of events, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey 
Kozyrev said today answering an ITAR-TASS correspondent's 
questions after meeting the Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen 
Manh Cam. 
  The head of the Russian foreign political department 
recalled 
that Russia had put forward a proposal to convene a multilateral 
conference on the security and non-nuclear status of the Korean 
peninsula, and it is currently being debated along with other 
ideas. There is a proposal to introduce sanctions. We believe 
that, unfortunately, this can happen but this would be an 
extremely unfavorable turn of events, as much as the DPRK's 
complete break with the nuclear nonproliferation regime, the 
Russian minister said. 
  That is why, he continued, we propose to hold a conference 
so 
that one does not have to resort to these extreme measures, 
although, of course, the situation is very alarming and the 
announcement of the DPRK leaving the IAEA is a highly negative 
event. 
  I must say, Kozyrev added, that IAEA guarantees are 
enshrined 
in the Treaty on the Nonproliferation of Nuclear Weapons and not 
in an agreement with the IAEA itself. I do not think that 
everything has already been lost and hope that the door is still 
ajar. That is why we think that the conference might give an 
opportunity to all its participants, including the DPRK, to find 
a better solution than the decision to break the 
nonproliferation regime, which will make confrontation with the 
world community unavoidable. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

