<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Churkin To Visit London for Talks on Bosnia </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Churkin To Visit London for Talks on Bosnia </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506142494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1250 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506142494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Boris Krivoshey] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 15 Jun--Russian Deputy Foreign Minister 
Vitaliy Churkin is flying to London today to discuss the whole 
range of problems connected with ways to settle the conflict in 
former Yugoslavia. He is expected to hold talks with 
representatives of the member states of the so-called "contact 
group." This was announced at a briefing today by Mikhail 
Demurin, deputy head of the Information and Press Department of 
the Russian Federation Foreign Ministry. 
  "The visit is to be viewed in the context of the overall 
efforts of the Russian Federation aimed at finding ways to a 
peaceful settlement in the region and at preparing a second 
meeting on Bosnia between the foreign ministers of Russia, the 
United States, and five countries of the European Union. The 
Russian side put forward the initiative to hold such a meeting 
some time ago," Demurin said. 

</TEXT>

