<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Pavel Kuznetsov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 15 TASS -- Russian Parliament Speaker 
Ivan Rybkin left for Germany on an official visit on Wednesday 
at the invitation of the Bundestag chairwoman Rita Suessmuth. 
  During the four-day visit the Russian delegation led by 
Rybkin plans to study the activity of the German parliament and 
exchange views on the development of interparliamentary 
relations between the two countries. 
  The agenda of the visit also includes meetings and talks 
with 
members of the German Government, the leaders of the leading 
political parties' factions in the German parliament. 
  Russian parliamentarians are also expected to visit one of 
the units of the western group of Russian troops. 

