<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Cited on Closer Cooperation With CIS </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Cited on Closer Cooperation With CIS </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606094994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0922 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606094994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Yuriy Kozlov and </F>
Boris Krivoshey] 
  [Text] Moscow June 16 TASS -- Russia would like to 
encourage closer cooperation and further integration between the 
country- members of the Commonwealth of Independent States. "We 
are ready for as much integration as our partners are", 
announced Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev on Thursday. 
  Speaking at a foreign policy council meeting devoted to the 
further integration of the CIS countries and to Russian 
interests, Kozyrev noted the appearance of a lot of far-reaching 
ideas which "show the urge for closer integration". "At the same 
time, we would like to avoid a situation in which the proposal 
and discussion of such promising ideas hinders us in resolving 
concrete pressing problems, or distracts our attention from 
them", Kozyrev said. 

</TEXT>

