<H3> <TI>   Admiral Denies Supply of `Low-Quality' Arms to Lithuania </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Admiral Denies Supply of `Low-Quality' Arms to Lithuania </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506212394 Vilnius Radio Vilnius in English 2100 GMT 15 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506212394 </F>
<F P=104>  Vilnius Radio Vilnius </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The chief commander of the Russian Baltic military 
fleet has said that the Lithuanian Defense Ministry was supplied 
with Russian armaments in accordance with an inter-governmental 
agreement, denying a number of allegations surrounding the 
transaction. 
  Admiral Vladimir Yegorov in his Wednesday interview to the 
Baltic News Service refuted accusations that Russia has supplied 
low- quality arms to Lithuania. A scandal broke out in 
Lithuania in March after searches were carried out in the flats 
of a number of former Defence Ministry officials and one man was 
arrested on charges of illegal actions when buying the armaments. 
  The Russian military official expressed his regret that 
these 
developments hampered Lithuanian-Russian relations. Admiral 
Yegorov also said, commenting on Russia's transit over Lithuania 
territory, that transit was vital to the Russian troops 
stationed in the Kaliningrad enclave. 

</TEXT>

