<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma 15 Jun Proceedings Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma 15 Jun Proceedings Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1606094794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 16 Jun 94 
First Edition p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1606094794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "Within Framework of Legal Norms"] </F>
  [Text] Yesterday the Russian State Duma deputies expressed 
concern in connection with the edict published Tuesday by 
President Boris Yeltsin on urgent measures in the struggle 
against crime. At the suggestion of Deputy Viktor Pokhmelkin 
from the "Russia's Choice" faction the chamber decided to 
analyze the head of state's document at a plenary session, 
having studied the edict beforehand in the relevant 
parliamentary committees. 
  In Viktor Pokhmelkin's opinion the edict contains violations 
of a number of legal norms. During the discussion of the motion 
as to whether the question of the president's edict should be 
put on the agenda, State Duma Chairman Ivan Rybkin stated that 
this document "must be accompanied by the relevant changes and 
additions to the criminal and criminal procedure codes" and by a 
relevant State Duma decree. 
  At the same session the deputies voted to hold a meeting of 
parliamentarians of Russia, Ukraine, and Belorussia [Belarus] on 
the question of the Belovezhskaya agreement and its results. 
The motion on this subject was submitted by Deputy Oleg Mironov 
in the form of a decree supplementing the agenda. 
  A decision was also made to invite Russian Defense Minister 
Pavel Grachev to the Duma on Friday to explain Russia's actions 
in fulfilling its peacekeeping mission in Georgia and Abkhazia 
and also Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev to explain the 
situation surrounding North Korea. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

