<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Liberal-Democratic Deputies Walk Out of Duma Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Liberal-Democratic Deputies Walk Out of Duma Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506164394 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1551 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506164394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Taranov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 15 TASS -- A group of deputies from the 
Liberal-Democratic Union "December 12th" walked out of the Duma 
session on Wednesday, saying they will not attend house hearings 
any more. 
  Speaking at a news conference, the deputies explained their 
decision by the fact that on June 13 the Committee for the 
Organisation of Work of the State Duma canceled the Union's 
registration, saying that it did not provide the required 35 
applications by the day of registration. 
  Union member Boris Fedorov denounced the move, describing it 
as a provocation. He accused the Duma factions of the Liberal 
Democratic Party and Russia's Choice of backstage intrigues in 
order to get rid of the "wrong" deputies. 
  He also blamed Russia's Choice faction for actions aimed 
against their own allies. 
  Irina Khokamada, another member of the Union, believes that 
the decision has shown that the Duma is excessively politicised. 

</TEXT>

