<H3> <TI>   Dudayev Wants Meeting With Yeltsin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dudayev Wants Meeting With Yeltsin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606092194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0725 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606092194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz, 16 June -- Today President Akhsarbek 
Galazov of the Republic of North Osetia met Shmidt Dzoblayev, a 
member of the public chamber under the president of the Russian 
Federation and secretary general of the Assembly of Democratic 
Forces of the North Caucasus, who has decided to act as 
intermediary in dialogue between the Russian and Chechen 
leadership. 
  The leader of the regional democratic movement told 
Akhsarbek 
Galazov that he had talked to the leadership of the Chechen 
Republic in Groznyy on 15 June. They discussed the restoration 
of normal relations with the Russian Federation, the role of 
Chechnya in settling Ossetian-Ingush relations, and ways to 
achieve stabilization in the North Caucasus region. 
  Shmidt Dzoblayev told the ITAR-TASS correspondent that 
Chechen President Dzhokhar Dudayev is ready to meet Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin and has said so many times. The Chechen 
side is considering establishing relations by treaty with Russia 
and is advocating the creation of guarantees against political 
repression. Dzhokhar Dudayev expressed readiness to promote the 
establishment of goodneighborly relations between the peoples of 
Chechnya, North Ossetia, and Ingushetia. 

</TEXT>

