<H3> <TI>   Kebich `Confident' That Union To Be Revived </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kebich `Confident' That Union To Be Revived </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1506125594 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 15 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK1506125594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Oleg Stepanenko: "Belorussia: Ever More Voices </F>
for Union"] 
  [Text] "I am confident that a renovated Union will be 
revived," said Vyacheslaw Kebich, chairman of the Republic's 
Council of Ministers, at a meeting with the collective of the 
Minsk Kirov Machine Tool Construction Plant. He underlined the 
special importance of unity with Russia: "Should we be left 
without Russia, it would be our ruin. One should be a realist 
in politics and remember that the wheel of history can only roll 
forward, not backward." 
  Millions of people see no life without a single union of 
fraternal peoples. In Belorussia [Belarus] nearly 
three-quarters of the citizens are for the revival. The most 
consistent supporters of restoring the Union of SSR on a new, 
mutually acceptable basis are Belorussian communists. It was 
they who proposed to hold the next meeting of representatives of 
the communist parties of the former USSR republics in Viskuli 
where the shameful Belovezhskaya Forest agreement was adopted. 

</TEXT>

