<H3> <TI>   Vitebsk Council To Urge Referendum on Russian Language </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vitebsk Council To Urge Referendum on Russian Language </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1606083194 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1606083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A session of the Vitebsk City Council has resolved 
to address the Supreme Soviet with a request to consider the 
possibility of holding a nationwide referendum regarding the 
issue of granting official status to the Russian language in 
Belarus. The reason for such an appeal to the highest 
legislative body was a poll conducted among Vitebsk residents, 
which was held by an initiative group. The poll showed that 
5,000 city residents support the idea of holding -- on the same 
day as presidential elections -- a city-wide referendum 
regarding the introduction of bilingualism. Such a stance is 
also supported [words indistinct] by 52 people's deputies in the 
Vitebsk City Council. 

</TEXT>

