Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minsk Notes Moscow Agreement on Duty-Free Oil, Gas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minsk Notes Moscow Agreement on Duty-Free Oil, Gas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1606080794 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 0300 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1606080794 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russian oil and gas will be supplied to Belarus 
duty free. This is the essence of a resolution, which has been 
adopted by the Government of the Russian Federation. The 
document, signed by Viktor Chernomyrdin, determines the 
mechanism for facilitating oil supplies, including condensed gas 
[hazavy kandensat] and products of oil refining, to Belarus. An 
assent was granted to the proposal of our Republic to extend 
Russian pricing policies to cover energy resources and raw 
materials to Belarusian economic bodies beginning from the 
moment the two countries' monetary systems are unified. 
Appropriate ministries and committees of the Russian Federation 
have been instructed to safeguard organizational measures for 
implementing this resolution, which is one of the first concrete 
steps toward the accomplishment of the agreement -- signed by 
Vyachaslaw Kebich and Viktor Chernomyrdin -- on the unification 
of the Belarusian and Russian monetary systems. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

