  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 11/6/1994 -- Yesterday's 
decision of the Parliament, according to which 24 August was 
declared the day of liberation, is an attempt to present events 
from the point of view of those who call themselves liberators, 
declared to BASA Alexandru Mosanu, leader of the Parliamentary 
Block of Peasants and Intellectuals. In Mosanu's opinion, the 
political aim of this decision was to induce more stress into 
the situation and to rehabilitate the communist occupational 
regime. The leader of the faction considers that the 
parliamentary majority "realizes the interests of those who keep 
an army of occupation on Moldovan territory." Characterizing 
the political situation in the republic, Mosanu stated that 
efforts are being made to reannex Moldova to the Russian Empire. 
"In this context, Parliament's decision yesterday is an attempt 
to falsify history," said Mosanu. 

