<F P=100> Moldova </F>
<H3> <TI>   Interior Ministry Takes Measures To Fight Crime </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Interior Ministry Takes Measures To Fight Crime </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506165994 Chisinau BASAPRESS in English 1939 GMT 11 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU1506165994 </F>
<F P=104>  Chisinau BASAPRESS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Chisinau, BASAPRESS, 11/6/1994 -- The Moldovan 
Ministry of Interior is carrying out for the third day "The 
Square" operation. Petru Harbur, head of the Chisinau Police 
Commissariat, stated to BASA that the main purpose of the 
operation is to stabilize the crime situation in Chisinau. 
According to him, there was a slight increase in the level of 
crime in the first quarter of 1994. Measures are undertaken to 
detect illegally held arms, criminals from the other regions of 
the CIS who have settled in Chisinau, cases of violation of 
passport regulations and raids on the usual criminal 
hang-outs-bars, casinos and restaurants. According to Harbur, 
the first two days of the operation resulted in a two fold 
decrease in the number of crimes. The police has detained four 
persons wanted by police and discovered illegally held arms. He 
said that forecasts about the efficiency of the operation are 
thus confirmed. 

</TEXT>

