<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Aliyev Meets With CSCE Minsk Group Delegation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aliyev Meets With CSCE Minsk Group Delegation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1506200294 Baku Radio Baku Network in Azeri 1700 GMT 15 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1506200294 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Radio Baku Network </F>
<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Geydar Aliyev received the visiting CSCE 
delegation headed by Jan Eliasson, chairman of the CSCE Minsk 
Group, today. Jan Eliasson recalled that today, 15 June, marks 
the first anniversary of Geydar Aliyev's return to Azerbaijan as 
a leading official after a long time and said that the 
Azerbaijan Government has taken important steps to end the war, 
which has continued for more than six years. He noted that the 
CSCE Minsk Group's close concern for the effort to end the war 
is the outcome of one of those steps. The guest stressed: 
Considering the proposals that have been recently made by the 
mediating countries and the UN organization and, in particular, 
focusing attention on the views expressed by the leading 
officials of Armenia and Azerbaijan, we are making an effort to 
end the war. [Words indistinct], that is the liberation of the 
occupied territories, return of the refugees to their homes, and 
restoration of the primary communications systems. That 
objective can be achieved only if the talks are maintained and 
the cease-fire agreement is heeded. 
  On his part, Geydar Aliyev said that Azerbaijan remains 
fully 
committed to the cease-fire in accordance with the agreement 
that was reached earlier. He said: We have stressed several 
times that we agree with the proposals that have been made by 
the UN organization, the CSCE, and other mediating countries for 
the finding of a peaceful solution to the Karabakh dispute. 
That we agree with those proposals should not be taken to mean 
that we will allow Azerbaijan's territorial integrity to be 
harmed. We support a just peace. We welcome the fact that the 
CSCE Minsk Group has recently adopted that concept in its 
activities. Azerbaijan's leaders have stressed in the talks 
that have been held on the question of the deployment of 
military observers in the region that the Armenians in Karabakh 
should not worry about their future when the Armenian military 
units begin to withdraw from the areas they have occupied. The 
UN and CSCE observers will give all the necessary guarantees to 
them. 
  Altan Karamanoglu, Turkey's ambassador in Baku and 
representative in the CSCE, attended the meeting. Speaker of 
the Azerbaijan National Assembly Rasul Guliyev; foreign policy 
adviser Vefa Gulizade; Foreign Minister Gasan Gasanov; Defense 
Minister Mamed- Rafi Mamedov; and other officials also attended 
the meeting. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

