<H3> <TI>   Supports Comprehensive Karabakh Agreement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supports Comprehensive Karabakh Agreement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506190294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1537 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Azeri President Geydar Aliyev favors the signing of 
a comprehensive political agreement, which would solve all 
problems associated with the Armenian-Azeri conflict in a just 
manner. 
  In line with the document, international forces or observers 
will be deployed in the region and the problem of security for 
Karabakh Armenians will be solved, said the president during the 
meeting in Baku on Wednesday with the chairman of the Minsk CSCE 
group, Jan Eliasson. 
  The president repeated the position of Azerbaijan according 
to which it is necessary to observe the cease-fire and achieve 
the liberation of the captured territory of Azerbaijan. 
  Aliyev accused Armenia of dual policies towards the 
Conference on Security and Cooperation in Europe, for example, 
of Yerevan's refusal to sign the CSCE plan for the conflict 
settlement, said the Azeri leader. 
  Eliasson said that the CSCE should act as a mediator in the 
settlement of the Armenian-Azeri conflict. 

</TEXT>

