<F P=103> LD1506133894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the evening of June 14 Abkhazia cut back by 80 
percent the supply to Georgia of electricity produced at the 
Inguri power station. 
  Vice Premier of the Abkhaz government, Vladimir Mikanba, 
told 
Interfax that this was in retaliation at the acts of sabotage 
carried out by Georgian forces in the Gali region of Abkhazia. 
Electricity cables were destroyed leading to a loss of supply to 
a number of regions, including the capital Sukhumi. 

</TEXT>

