<H3> <TI>   Request for Assault Proceedings Against Zhirinovskiy Denied </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Request for Assault Proceedings Against Zhirinovskiy Denied </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1506123594 Moscow KURANTY in Russian 15 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> MK1506123594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KURANTY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Yan Ulanskiy report under the "Scandal" rubric: "There Is </F>
No Keeping V.V. Zh. in Check"] 
  [Text] Moscow's law and order organs gave the LDPR 
[Liberal Democratic Party of Russia] a remarkable gift for 
Russian Independence Day. 
  The Investigations Directorate of the Moscow Main Internal 
Affairs Administration has turned down a request to start 
criminal proceedings against Zhirinovskiy from State Duma 
deputies and a STOLITSA magazine journalist who were injured by 
V.V. Zh. [Vladimir Volfovich Zhirinovskiy] on 8 April (owing to 
the absence of corpus delicti). Thus, the LDPR leader gets 
carte blanche to use the physiognomies of his political 
opponents to relieve the itch in his fists. According to 
KURANTY, however, the State Duma deputies do not intend to give 
up attempts to get Zhirinovskiy punished, even if not by court, 
for the fight in the Duma in April. 

</TEXT>

