<H3> <TI>   Prosecutor Asks Duma To Repeal Zhirinovskiy Immunity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Prosecutor Asks Duma To Repeal Zhirinovskiy Immunity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506134894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1117 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506134894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Taranov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 15 TASS--The acting prosecutor general 
Alexey Ilyushenko has lodged an appeal with the State Duma, 
asking to deprive the LDP [Liberal Democratic Party] leader 
Vladimir Zhirinovskiy of his parliamentary immunity. 
  The request was made in connection with the fact that the 
Russian prosecutor's general office believes that Zhirinovskiy's 
book entitled "The Last Breakthrough to the South" gives grounds 
for instituting criminal proceedings against Zhirinovskiy. This 
was announced by the chairman of the State Duma, Ivan Rybkin, at 
its session today. 
  The Duma Council is expected to look into the appeal on 
Thursday. 

</TEXT>

