<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Package of Housing Edicts Published </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Package of Housing Edicts Published </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Edict on Completing Unfinished Apartment Blocks </H4>

<F P=102> PM1506103394 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 15 Jun 94 
First Edition p 3 </F>

<F P=103> PM1506103394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation President's Edict No. 1181 "On Measures </F>
To Ensure the Completion of Construction of Unfinished Apartment 
Blocks"] 
  [Text] With a view to creating conditions for providing 
housing for Russian Federation citizens, reducing the volumes of 
expenditure on maintaining uncompleted apartment blocks, and 
ensuing their completion and commissioning, I decree: 
  1. That it be established that uncompleted apartment blocks 
under federal ownership, including those under the full economic 
management of enterprises and the operational management of 
organizations and institutions and whose construction was ended 
or suspended in connection with the absence of the necessary 
federal budget financing this year are subject to being 
transferred for the completion of construction or to being sold. 
  The decision to transfer for the completion of construction 
or to sell uncompleted apartment blocks which were ordered by 
federal organs of executive power and organizations and 
institutions financed from the federal budget is made by the 
Russian Federation State Committee for Questions of Architecture 
and Construction and the Russian Federation State Committee for 
the Administration of State Property in agreement with the 
organs of executive power of the Russian Federation components. 
  The decision to transfer for the completion of construction 
or to sell uncompleted apartment blocks ordered by federal state 
enterprises is made upon representation from the client 
enterprise by the Russian Federation State Committee for the 
Administration of State property and the Russian Federation 
State Committee for Questions of Architecture and Construction 
by agreement with the RUssian Federation components' organs of 
executive power. 
  2. That the federal state enterprises which ordered the 
construction of apartment blocks whose construction has been 
halted or suspended in connection with the lack of the necessary 
financing be allowed to transfer to subcontracting organizations 
for completion or to sell uncompleted apartment blocks. 
  3. That it be established that the transfer for the 
completion of construction and the sale of uncompleted apartment 
blocks is implemented exclusively at investment and commercial 
competitions with a view to ensuring the speediest completion of 
apartment blocks and the provision of housing for citizens. 
  4. That it be established that the attached statute on the 
procedure for transferring uncompleted apartment blocks and for 
selling them be approved. 
  5. That it be recommended to the organs of executive power 
of the Russian Federation components and the organs of local 
self-management that they make the decision to transfer for the 
completion of construction or to sell apartment blocks under, 
respectively, the state ownership of components of the Russian 
Federation and municipal ownership. 
  6. That this edict enters into force from the moment it is 
published. 
  [signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin, Moscow, 
Kremlin, 10 June 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

