<H3> <TI>   Package of Housing Edicts Published </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Package of Housing Edicts Published </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Edict on Housing Certificates </H4>

<F P=102> PM1506105794 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 15 Jun 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1506105794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation president's Edict No. 1182 "On the Issue </F>
and Circulation of Housing Certificates"] 
  [Text] With a view to expanding the use of funds owned by 
the population and from other nonbudget sources of financing in 
the housing sphere and protecting them from inflation I decree: 
  1. That it be established that the corporate bodies with the 
rights of clients when constructing apartment blocks, a land 
plot allocated within the established procedure for housing 
construction, and planning documents for housing construction 
have the right to attract funds from citizens of the Russian 
Federation using housing certificates. 
  2. That the attached statute on the issue and circulation of 
housing certificates be approved. 
  3. That the Russian Federation Government submit before 1 
August 1994 to the Federal Assembly State Duma a draft law on 
the procedure for taxing operations involving housing 
certificates. 
  4. The Russian Federation Ministry of Finances and the 
Russian Federation State Committee for Questions of Architecture 
and Construction must elaborate and approve within two months an 
Instruction on the procedure for the issue and circulation of 
housing certificates and also for their repayment, including 
through the provision of housing for their owners. 
  5. This edict enters into force from the moment it is 
published. 
  [signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin, Moscow, 
Kremlin, 10 June 1994. 

</TEXT>

