<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Economic Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chubays on Post-Voucher Privatization </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chubays on Post-Voucher Privatization </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506185694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1537 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506185694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The validity of vouchers will not be prolonged after 
June 30 and President Yeltsin may sign a decree on post-voucher 
privatization soon, Vice-Premier, Chairman of the RF State 
Property Committee Anatoliy Chubays said. 
  Interviewed by the Financial Information Agency on 
Wednesday, 
Chubays said that the program for post-voucher privatization 
approved by the government was to be submitted to President 
Yeltsin for signature no later than June 25. 
  Chubays said that the bulk of funds (51 percent) raised by 
the post-voucher privatization beginning on July 1 would be left 
to the enterprises. 
  About the mechanism of post-voucher privatization 
Vice-Premier said that simultaneously with the presidential 
decree effecting it the program would be presented to the State 
Duma for consideration. 
  Chubays said that discounts to staffs were one of the key 
features of monetary privatization. 
  Two types of discounts are planned. Under one option the 
employees will receive no more than 25 percent of privileged 
shares giving no right to vote free. Under the other the 
employees will be able to buy out 10 percent of simple (voting) 
actions at a 30 percent discount. The starting price of shares 
is expected to grow 600 to 700 percent, because the assets will 
be evaluated in January 1, 1994 prices. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

