<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Military, Nuclear &amp; Space Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kokoshin Terms Defense Budget `Unacceptable' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kokoshin Terms Defense Budget `Unacceptable' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506204194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1827 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506204194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey Kokoshin has 
described Russia's military expenditure for 1994 as totally 
unacceptable and absurd. Kokoshin took part in a nationwide 
conference on the development of avionics in St. Petersburg 
Wednesday. 
  Kokoshin told Interfax that the budget proposed by the State 
Duma would not only fail to lead the defense industries out of 
the standstill, but would completely ruin them. 
  Pointing out that Russia could still trade arms, including 
warships, Kokoshin said that the problem was to find a buyer 
rather than to sell the equipment at a profit. 
  During his stay in St. Petersburg, Kokoshin visited the 
holding company Leninets, developing military electronic 
products, and the dock Severnye Verfi to see the construction of 
several warships. 
  Kokoshin is leaving for Minsk to meet Belarusian Prime 
Minister Vyacheslav Kebich on June 16. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

