<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hryb, Cuban Delegation Discuss Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hryb, Cuban Delegation Discuss Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1506144494 Minsk Radio Minsk Network in Belarusian 1000 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> WS1506144494 </F>
<F P=104>  Minsk Radio Minsk Network </F>
<F P=105>  Belarusian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Belarusian Supreme Soviet Chairman Myacheslaw Hryb 
has received an official governmental delegation from the 
Republic of Cuba, led by Council of Ministers Vice President 
Lionel Soto Prieto. In the course of talks, Myacheslaw Hryb 
pointed out that Belarus is interested in consolidating and 
expanding economic cooperation with Cuba, which, unfortunately, 
is currently developing at quite a sluggish pace. The speaker 
believes problems of mutual payments are among the causes for 
that situation. According to him, however, this problem can 
also be resolved, given that not only Belarus has great interest 
in Cuban products but Cuba is also interested in Belarusian 
goods. The two sides agreed that in the near future it will be 
necessary to organize the work of experts who will draft 
economic agreements for 1995. In the course of the visit, the 
members of the Cuban delegation also held talks with 
representatives of the Ministry of Trade and the Ministry of 
External Economic Relations. 

</TEXT>

