<H3> <TI>   Zlenko Comments on DPRK Withdrawal From IAEA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zlenko Comments on DPRK Withdrawal From IAEA </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506131694 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1044 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506131694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] North Korea will have to face hard times, Ukrainian 
Foreign Minister Anatoliy Zlenko told journalists on Tuesday [14 
June]. 
  Commenting on the decision of North Korea to cease its 
participation in the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA], 
Zlenko said he believed it would be very difficult to confront 
the whole world community which stands for the elimination of 
nuclear weapons. 
  Zlenko repeated that the position of Ukraine had been made 
clear during the recent visit of the North Korean foreign 
minister. He said Ukraine was hoping that North Korea was 
moving towards a non-nuclear status. On this basis, Kiev is 
ready to cooperate with North Korea, Zlenko added. 

</TEXT>

