<H3> <TI>   United States Offers Mediation in Black Sea Fleet Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    United States Offers Mediation in Black Sea Fleet Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606095794 Kiev UNIAN in Ukrainian 0745 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606095794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAN </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev [no date as received]--Ukrainian Defense 
Minister Vitaliy Radetskyy is continuing his official visit to 
the United States. During a meeting between the Ukrainian and 
U.S. defense ministers on 14 June, the U.S. side again 
emphasized its willingness to mediate between Ukraine and Russia 
on the division of the Black Sea Fleet, the press service of 
Ukraine's Ministry of Defense reports. 
  Radetskyy and William Perry also discussed the 
implementation 
of the trilateral statement by the presidents of Ukraine, the 
United States, and Russia. The Ukrainian defense minister noted 
that the work on the withdrawal of nuclear arms from Ukraine was 
proceeding in strict accordance with the schedule. 
  The sides also discussed the Partnership for Peace program 
and joint training between the two states' subdivisions at 
various levels. On 15 June, Radetskyy and Perry plan to visit a 
naval base in Norfolk and meet with NATO Supreme Allied 
Commander Atlantic David Miller. 

</TEXT>

