<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ready To Meet With Christopher </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ready To Meet With Christopher </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606112094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1046 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606112094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 16 Jun (TASS) -- Russian Foreign Minister 
Andrey Kozyrev today confirmed that he was prepared to meet U.S. 
Secretary of State Warren Christopher in the near future to 
agree on a common approach to a settlement of the situation on 
the Korean peninsula. An accord on such a meeting of the heads 
of the foreign policy departments of the two countries was 
reached in the course of the telephone conversation the other 
day between Boris Yeltsin and Bill Clinton. 
  Speaking in a talk with journalists about the date for this 
dialogue, Andrey Kozyrev said, among other things: "As for the 
meeting of ministers of which the presidents spoke, I proposed 
to my friend and colleague Warren Christopher specific dates for 
this meeting, and I am awaiting a reply from him on specific 
dates. It goes without saying that I am prepared to meet in the 
nearest future and at a time convenient for both sides, in order 
to continue the work as the presidents agreed, that is, to work 
out a joint approach to this extraordinarily complicated 
question." 

</TEXT>

