<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Treaty Signing Postponed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Treaty Signing Postponed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606111194 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1002 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606111194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Andrey Bychkov and </F>
Andrey Kirillov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 16 Jun (TASS) -- Talks between Russian Prime 
Minister Viktor Chernomyrdin and Vo Van Kiet, the Prime Minister 
of the SRV Government, were concluded at noon today. 
Incidentally, the signing of the treaty on the basis of 
friendly relations between the two countries and other 
documents, which was expected immediately after the conclusion 
of talks, has been postponed until this evening. 
  Answering an ITAR-TASS correspondent's question, Viktor 
Chernomyrdin stated that "in fact, there are no disagreements 
between us." Explaining the delay regarding the signing of 
Russian- Vietnamese documents, the head of the Russian 
Government noted that during a discussion "technicalities" 
arose, which require further work on the part of specialists. 
Thus, he added, the signing is being postponed until this 
evening. "We are convinced," Chernomyrdin stressed, "that we and 
Vietnam have all the possibilities and potential to increase 
traditional cooperation in the trade-economic, technical, 
scientific -- as well as other -- spheres". 
  For his part, Vo Van Kiet agreed with the assessment of the 
talks given by the Russian prime minister and added: "We need 
some time to better prepare these documents." 
  ITAR-TASS correspondents have learned from well-informed 
sources close to the Vietnamese delegation that disagreements in 
the position of the sides arose on the following issues: the 
problem of settling the debt of Vietnam to Russia, which the 
latter inherited from the former USSR, the conditions for the 
Russian Navy's use of the base of Cam Ranh, and a range of 
issues relating to Vietnamese citizens residing in Russia. 

</TEXT>

