<F P=103> LD1506181994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow 15 June TASS -- The Tajik Defence Ministry 
commanded today an operation aimed at the liquidation of the 
opposition armed groups near the settlement of Garm, where 
Deputy Minister Ramazan Radjabov was killed early in the morning 
on Wednesday. 
  According to the ministry, Radjabov and his escort were 
moving along a village road in two vehicles when they were 
suddenly found themselves under automatic fire from an ambush 
laid by a group of Islamic opposition. 
  The deputy minister, Captain S. Khokhlov and four soldiers 
from Radjabov's escort were killed on the spot, one was injured 
and is now in bad condition, the source told TASS. 

</TEXT>

