<F P=100> Tajikistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Officer Died in Accident, Not Shot </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Officer Died in Accident, Not Shot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506111494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0951 
GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1506111494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Galina Gridneva] </F>
  [Text] Dushanbe, 15 Jun (ITAR-TASS) -- The law enforcement 
bodies of Tajikistan have set out their version of the death of 
30-year-old Senior Lieutenant Mikhail Osipov, company commander 
of the 191st Russian Motorized Infantry Regiment stationed in 
the city of Kurgan-Tyube and forming part of the 201st Motorized 
Infantry Division. 
  The ITAR-TASS correspondent was told by Major-General 
Gennadiy Blinov, the Republic's first deputy minister of 
internal affairs, that the Russian officer died as a result of 
an accident right on the territory of the military unit, and was 
not shot by unidentified persons during an alleged evening 
patrol check in one of the city's streets. The Republic's law 
enforcement bodies are presently carefully investigating this 
tragic incident, Gennadiy Blinov stressed. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

