<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk on Nomination </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk on Nomination </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506113594 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1102 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506113594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 15 June TASS -- Ukrainian President Leonid 
Kravchuk has proposed making Vitaliy Masol, 66, Ukraine's new 
prime minister. A member of the Ukrainian parliament, Masol was 
the last head of the Ukrainian Government under communists. 
  Earlier he worked for 20 years at the Novokramatorsk 
machine-building plant, rising from assistant foreman to general 
director. He later worked on the state planning committee and 
headed the Ukrainian Government until October 1990 when he 
resigned in protest against the political and economic course 
approved by the then parliament under pressure from national 
democrats. 
  In the present parliament Vitaliy Masol has no party 
affiliation, although he says he remains "a communist at heart." 
The former premier has a good chance of regaining the post, 
because the communist majority in the parliament is expected to 
back his candidature. 
  Vitaliy Masol will present his programme to the parliament 
within the next few days. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

