<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Elected by Secret Ballot </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Elected by Secret Ballot </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606083194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0806 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606083194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Kiev 16 June TASS -- Secret voting is to be held in 
the Ukrainian parliament on Thursday [16 June] on the 
endorsement of Vitaliy Masol's appointment as Ukrainian prime 
minister. The parliament adopted this decision on Wednesday 
after a programme statement by the candidate to the post of 
prime minister. 
  Masol, specifically, said he believes "Ukraine must continue 
developing as an independent democratic rule-of-law state. The 
strengthening of its sovereignity and preservation of 
territorial integrity should be common concern". Masol believes 
"Ukraine needs equal and friendly relations with countries of 
the CIS and above all with Russia in order to preserve its own 
independence". 
  Masol holds that to overcome the crisis it is necessary to 
step up the pace of economic reform, transfer to market 
relations and ensure equality of all forms of property. The 
government should ease taxation on entrepreneurial structures 
engaged in production and processing of farm produce, in the 
construction industry and in communal services. 
  Masol believes that support by credits, banking services on 
easy terms and ensurance against commercial risks should be 
offered to these areas. He said that the main purpose now is 
not to levy exorbitant taxes and drawing up an unrealistic basis 
but to ease taxation and envigorate the economy, enabling work 
collectives to work calmly and people to receive their earnings. 
Masol believes taxes should not exceed 17 percent of profits. 
  He said there are two approaches to land privatisation. Land 
can be rented for the construction of various social facilities 
for 49 years, also to foreign investors, or else land can be 
offered for long-term use with the right of inheritance. 
  Masol expressed the conviction that it takes the effort of 
all branches of power to solve all problems. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

