<H3> <TI>   Navy Accuses Black Sea Fleet Command of Removing Property </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Navy Accuses Black Sea Fleet Command of Removing Property </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506181594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1537 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506181594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commander of the Ukrainian Navy Volodymyr 
Bezkorovaynyy accused the Black Sea Fleet commanders of removing 
property from the garrisons, which are to belong to Ukraine. He 
told INTERFAX-Ukraine on Wednesday [15 June] that the Black Sea 
Fleet commanders hoped to make the property of the Black Sea 
Fleet Russia's property. 
  "The removal of the property will inflict direct damage on 
the economic interests of Ukraine," said Bezkorovaynyy. 
  In his opinion, this question must be discussed during the 
next round of the Ukrainian-Russian talks on the division of the 
Black Sea Fleet. 
  He also announced that the headquarters of the Ukrainian 
Navy 
were considering the parameters of the Russian fleet's temporary 
stay in Sevastopol. 
  He said that the discussion of the division of the logistics 
property continued. 

</TEXT>

