<H3> <TI>   Water Leaking From Chernobyl Processed Fuel Storage Unit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Water Leaking From Chernobyl Processed Fuel Storage Unit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1506161894 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1348 GMT 15 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1506161894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two cubic meters of water continue to leak every 
hour from a storage facility in the second power unit of the 
Chernobyl station, its chief engineer Viktor Vasilchenko told 
INTERFAX-Ukraine. 
  The leakage from the storage of processed nuclear fuel was 
detected on 11 June. 
  Vasilchenko said the leakage resulted from the way storage 
facilities of this kind had been installed. 
  Vasilchenko also said that the heating elements would be 
removed from the storage before Friday and the source of leakage 
would be found soon after. He thought that even if the storage 
facility was destroyed, nothing serious would happen. 
  Alexander Yelchishchev, chief of a shift in the station, had 
told INTERFAX-Ukraine that radiation in neighboring premises was 
normal. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

