<H3> <TI>   Official: Situation `Normal' Despite Leak </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official: Situation `Normal' Despite Leak </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506145394 Kiev URYADOVYY KURYER in Ukrainian 14 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1506145394 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev URYADOVYY KURYER </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by UKRINFORM correspondents Viktor Demydenko and </F>
Mykhaylo Melnyk in Kiev on 10 June: "The Radiation Situation Is 
Normal"] 
  [Text] An insignificant increase in the technological leak 
of contaminated water from the reservoir where used-fuel 
cassettes are stored was recorded at the Chernobyl Atomic 
Electric Power Plant [AES]. This was stated by Serhiy 
Nazarenko, chief of the emergency and control administration of 
Ukraine's State Committee for Atomic Energy. According to him, 
the controlled system of drainage of technological waters, 
preventing their escape into the environment, guarantees the 
reliable accumulation of contaminated waters and their 
processing. At present, the radiation situation at the 
Chernobyl AES is normal, he assured. 

</TEXT>

