<F P=106> [Report by Grigoriy Nesmyanovich: "Ukrainian Officers Union </F>
Has Admitted There Will Be Spectacles in Addition to Exercises 
in the Army"] 
  [Text] Kiev -- The Sixth Congress of the Ukrainian 
Officers Union has been held here. 
  An appeal to the Ukrainian Supreme Council was prepared at 
the congress calling for preservation of Ukraine's nuclear 
status. A number of complaints at the congress were directed at 
the Ukrainian president and especially at the defense minister. 
Army General Vitaliy Radetskyy was reproached for the decline 
of combat readiness and discipline, the increase in the number 
of military crimes, and for the unprecedented increase in the 
number of generals and "showcase" exercises, all of which had no 
parallels in the Soviet period. 

</TEXT>

