<H3> <TI>   Ministry To Scrap Missile Carrier `Varyah' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry To Scrap Missile Carrier `Varyah' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506164694 Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 14 Jun 94 p 4 </F>
<F P=103> AU1506164694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev HOLOS UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "The Missile Carrier Varyah Will Be </F>
Scrapped"] 
  [Text] The missile carrier Varyah will be scrapped. This 
decision was adopted on 2 June by the board of Ukraine's 
Ministry of Machine Building, Military-Industrial Complex and 
Conversion. Ukrainian Vice Prime Minister Valeriy Shmarov, in an 
interview for journalists on 9 June called the decision "forced 
and tragic." In the past, Ukraine offered Russia to purchase 
the still unfinished cruiser that stands near the moorings of 
the Black Sea Ship Building Plant in Nikolayev, but there was no 
response. 

</TEXT>

