<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Babych Opposes Building of Odessa Oil Terminal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU1506193594 Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY in Ukrainian 14 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> AU1506193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev MOLOD UKRAYINY </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report published under the rubric "Fact"] </F>
  [Text] In the opinion of Ukrainian presidential candidate 
Valeriy Babych, it is inexpedient to build the oil terminal in 
Odessa, as, having spent billions of dollars, Ukraine may find 
itself totally dependent upon oil-producing countries. He 
believes that it would be more expedient to lease from Russia or 
to redeem some of the oil field in the Tyumen Region, where 
Ukraine took part in oil exploration. 

</TEXT>

