GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606101694 </F>
<F P=104>  Dushanbe Radio Tajikistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Tajik </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Two vehicles carrying servicemen from the Tajik 
Defense Ministry, who were on their way to Khait village to 
fulfill their duties, [words indistinct] came under fire last 
night. As a result, six persons were killed and [word 
indistinct] were wounded. 
  As a result of these actions Colonel Ramazan Rajabov, deputy 
defense minister of the Republic of Tajikistan, and Captain S. 
Kholov, officer of the Defense Ministry's directorate, were 
killed. The leadership of the Republic's Defense Ministry 
expresses its deep condolences to the families and close 
relatives of those killed. The people of the Republic of 
Tajikistan have lost their [word indistinct] sons in defense of 
this province and [words indistinct] 

