<F P=100> RUSSIA NATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Political Issues </F>
<H3> <TI>   ITAR-TASS Claims Grenade Thrown at Moscow Bank </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ITAR-TASS Claims Grenade Thrown at Moscow Bank </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606142794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1403 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 16 [TASS] -- A grenade was thrown at the 
window of the "Obyedinyonny bank" (United Bank) of Moscow at 
four o'clock this afternoon [1200 GMT]. Preliminary reports 
state that some people have been injured by the resulting blast 
in the bank on Arbat street. In particular, one woman was cut 
by slivers of glass. 
  The Obyedinyonny Bank was registed by the Russian Federation 
Central Bank on January 2, 1992, and has a license to perform 
all banking operations on Russian territory and abroad. 
  The bank's 1993 turnover in roubles and foreign currency was 
reported to be 366.6 billion roubles (about 334 million U.S. 
dollars). The bank has correspondent accounts in Finland, 
Germany, Great Britain and Switzerland. 

</TEXT>

