<H3> <TI>   Edict on Regional Representatives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict on Regional Representatives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1706100394 Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI in Russian 16 Jun 94 p 
2 </F>

<F P=103> PM1706100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKIYE VESTI </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Edict No. 1186 of the Russian Federation President "On the </F>
Powers of Representatives of the Russian Federation President in 
Russian Federation Components," dated Moscow, the Kremlin, 10 
June 1994 and signed by Russian Federation President Boris 
Yeltsin] 
  [Text] In connection with the need to establish the status 
of representatives of the Russian Federation president in 
republics, krays, oblasts, cities of federal significance, the 
autonomous oblast, and autonomous okrugs, in accordance with the 
Russian Federation Constitution and on the basis of Article 83 
of the Russian Federation Constitution, I decree that: 
  The Russian Federation president's representatives in the 
republics appointed at an earlier date under RSFSR presidential 
directive No. 34-rp "On Approving the Temporary Statute 
Regarding the RSFSR President's Representatives in Republics 
Within the RSFSR," and also the Russian Federation president's 
representatives in the krays, oblasts, cities of federal 
significance, the autonomous oblast, and autonomous okrugs 
appointed at an earlier date under Russian Federation 
presidential edict No. 186 "On the Russian Federation 
President's Representatives in Krays, Oblasts, the Autonomous 
Oblast, Autonomous Okrugs, and the Cities of Moscow and St. 
Petersburg" dated 5 February 1993 are to be regarded as 
plenipotentiary representatives of the Russian Federation 
president in the appropriate Russian Federation components. 
  [Signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin 
  Moscow, the Kremlin 
  10 June 1994 
  No. 1186 

</TEXT>

