<H3> <TI>   Edict on Stimulating Investment Activity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Edict on Stimulating Investment Activity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1606125194 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 16 Jun 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1606125194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation President's Edict No. 1199 "On Some </F>
Measures To Stimulate Investment Activity Including Activity 
Involving the Enlistment of Foreign Credits"] 
  [Text] With a view to developing national industry and 
supporting enterprises' investment activity I decree: 
  1. That it be established that enterprises, institutions, 
and organizations which import onto Russian Federation territory 
equipment, machinery, and mechanisms (except for those liable to 
excise duty) intended for the production development of 
enterprises, institutions, and organizations under contracts 
concluded before 1 January 1993 and registered within the 
established procedure are exempt in 1994 from the payment of 
value-added tax or the special tax for the maintenance of the 
most important sectors of the national economy. 
  Sums paid before the adoption of this edict in value-added 
tax and special tax are subject to reimbursement to enterprises, 
institutions, and organizations within the procedure established 
by point 16 of the Russian Federation president's 22 December 
1993 Edict No. 2270. 
  2. That it be established that value-added tax and the 
special tax for the maintenance of the most important sectors of 
the national economy are not levied when goods (except for goods 
liable to excise duty) are imported onto the territory of the 
Russian Federation within the framework of the use of credits 
supplied to the Russian Federation by the governments of foreign 
states and international finance organizations or of goods 
(except for goods liable to excise duty) imported to pay off 
state credits supplied to foreign states by the former USSR and 
by the Russian Federation. 
  3. That the Russian Federation Government submit for 
examination by the Russian Federation Federal Assembly the 
drafts of legislative acts stemming from the clauses of this 
edict. 
  4. This edict enters into force from the moment it is 
published. 
  [signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin, Moscow, 
Kremlin, 10 June 1994. 

</TEXT>

