<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Sergey Ostanin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow, 17 June -- A naval detachment of the Black 
Sea Fleet has today begun practicing joint tasks with the 
Russian group of troops in western Georgia. It will take part 
in the peacekeeping operation to stabilize the situation in this 
region, ITAR-TASS was told at the Fleet's press center. Rear 
Admiral Yuriy Chichik, head of the Black Sea Fleet command 
center, will be in command of the operation. 
  According to the press center's information, a naval 
detachment of the Black Sea Fleet, with the large antisubmarine 
vessel Kerch as flagship, has left for the Greek island of Corfu 
tasked with preparing for the Russian president's visit. The 
detachment is under command of Rear Admiral Anatoliy Manchenko, 
first deputy head of Fleet Headquarters. 

