<H3> <TI>   Expedition to Sunken Komsomolets Sub Starts 16 Jun </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Expedition to Sunken Komsomolets Sub Starts 16 Jun </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1706084394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 16 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1706084394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report from Own Information-RIA Column: "By Mir to the </F>
Komsomolets"] 
  [Text] Kaliningrad -- On board the scientific research 
ship Akademik Mstislav Keldysh in the Norwegian Sea the 
preparations for the fourth international expedition to the 
Komsomolets nuclear submarine have been completed. The ship has 
Mir apparatuses aboard, which will enable the research staff to 
reach a depth of 6,000 meters. 
  "The expedition is beginning on 16 June and will take two 
months. Our main task is to obtain new data on the present 
condition of the submarine, guarantee its safety in terms of 
radioactivity, and install new one-year observation stations," 
Oleg Kuznetsov, the expedition's deputy chief, said. 

</TEXT>

