<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chechnya Asks for Flight Resumption </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chechnya Asks for Flight Resumption </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606195294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1833 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606195294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Chechen Foreign Ministry called on the Russian 
Transportation Ministry to resume flights from Moscow to Groznyy 
that were suspended ostensibly for security considerations. 
  The ministry's letter emphasized that the situation was 
quiet 
in Groznyy. 
  The Chechen Foreign Ministry described the unilateral 
suspension of flights by Moscow as a violation of international 
law which does serious harm to bilateral relations. 

</TEXT>

