<DATE1>  16 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Promises 1,000 Combine Harvesters to Novosibirsk </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Promises 1,000 Combine Harvesters to Novosibirsk </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606135494 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1308 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606135494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Viktor Yelmakov] </F>
  [Text] Novosibirsk, 16 June -- Russian President Boris 
Yeltsin made a stopover in Novosibirsk this afternoon on the way 
to Moscow from eastern Russia. 
  Boris Yeltsin had a conversation with leaders of the oblast. 
During the conversation, Ivan Indinok, head of the oblast 
administration, said important problems in the oblast were 
touched on. He assessed the conversation with the president as 
very interesting and full. The head of administration said that 
the president had agreed to a request to send a government 
commission to the oblast to work with local experts on an 
analysis of the functioning of the administration and to 
consider aid issues. 
  Boris Yeltsin also asked about the outcome of the sowing 
season and expressed concern about the difficulty in harvesting. 
Ivan Indinok asked for combines to be sent to Novosibirsk, as 
the pool of vehicles is going to be greatly overloaded. 
  The president gave an instruction that sending a thousand 
combines to the oblast should be considered. This would be a 
tremendous support for us, the head of adminstration said about 
the president's decision. 
  After a short stopover the president's airplane left for 
Moscow. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

