<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Law Gives Tatar President Extra Authority </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Law Gives Tatar President Extra Authority </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   944F0830A Kazan RESPUBLIKA TATARSTAN in Russian 15 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> 944F0830A </F>
<F P=104>  Kazan RESPUBLIKA TATARSTAN </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
CSO 

<F P=106> ["Law of the Tatarstan Republic: On Endowing the President </F>
of the Tatarstan Republic With Additional Authority in 
Connection With the Socioeconomic Situation That Has Taken Shape 
in the Tatarstan Republic"] 
  [Text] With the aim of enhancing the operational 
effectiveness of decisionmaking in the economy, of securing the 
further course of reforms in the Tatarstan Republic, and of 
strengthening social protection for the populace, and in 
accordance with Point 17 of Article 111 and Article 112 of the 
Constitution of the Tatarstan Republic, the Supreme Soviet of 
the Tatarstan Republic decrees: 
  Article 1. To extend to the president of the 
Tatarstan Republic, until such time as appropriate laws 
regulating legal relations in the financial, economic, social, 
and administrative spheres of the Tatarstan Republic are 
adopted, the right to issue edicts with respect to the 
above-mentioned issues. 
  Article 2. This law enters into force as of its 
date of publication and remains in effect until 1 April 1995. 
  [Signed]President of the Tatarstan Republic M. Shaymiyev 
  City of Kazan, 8 June 1994 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

