<H3> <TI>   Ivanov Patriotic, Youth Groups Flog U.S. Flag </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ivanov Patriotic, Youth Groups Flog U.S. Flag </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   MK1606123094 Moscow PRAVDA in Russian 16 Jun 94 p 2 </F>
<F P=103> MK1606123094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow PRAVDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed "Own Information" report: "A U.S. Flag Has </F>
Been Flogged"] 
  [Text] Representatives of youth, patriotic, and left-wing 
organizations in the city of Ivanov have staged a public 
flogging of a U.S. flag. It was flogged with birch rods, 
"indiscriminately, at whatever part came to hand." People say 
that it would be much better to flog a live American. He would 
be screaming and shouting, twisting and rolling, and doing many 
amusing things. 
  Cruel? Possibly. But one can well understand these people, 
driven to despair and sick with the "good life U.S.-style" being 
foisted on them by TV. 

