<F P=100> CENTRAL ASIA </F>
<F P=101> Kazakhstan </F>
<H3> <TI>   President Chairs Security Council Session </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    President Chairs Security Council Session </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606151494 Almaty Kazakh Radio Network in Kazakh 1400 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Almaty Kazakh Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Kazakh </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A regular session of the Security Council was held 
today chaired by Nursultan Nazarbayev. Under discussion were 
the issues of provision of the armed forces of the Republic of 
Kazakhstan with weapons, material and technical resources, a 
concept for formation and implementation of long term defense 
program, and the development of the defense complex of the 
Republic of Kazakhstan. Minister of Defense Sagadat 
Nurmugamabetov and Minister of Economy Mark Urkimbayev addressed 
those present. The president of Kazakhstan summarized the 
results of the discussion. The Security Council endorsed the 
concept for the formation and use of long term defense programs 
and the development of defense complex. It also approved 
certain changes in its composition. In particular it approved 
Bulat Baykenov as its secretary. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

