<F P=100> WESTERN REGION </F>
<F P=101> Belarus </F>
<H3> <TI>   Agreement Reached With Russians on Arms Deliveries </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Agreement Reached With Russians on Arms Deliveries </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606193194 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1833 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The mutual payments for delivered and repaired 
military equipment between the armed forces of Russia and 
Belarus will be performed at prices set for the two countries' 
own armies, Russian First Deputy Defense Minister Andrey 
Kokoshin told a news conference in Minsk Thursday [16 June]. 
  He said that according to a protocol signed with Belarussian 
First Deputy Defense Minister Aleksandr Tushinskiy Thursday all 
contracts between the two countries' military enterprises will 
be concluded directly, without mediators. This will enable both 
countries to significantly reduce their military expenditures. 
  For his part, Tushinskiy pointed to the importance of the 
agreement to start bilateral consultations on the utilization of 
components of the fuel used for surface-to-air missiles and 
bombs. At present, Belarus lacks its own technologies and 
equipment for this, Tushinskiy said. 
  Representatives of the two countries' commands supported the 
creation of joint military enterprises and financial and 
industrial groups to manufacture a wide range of products. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

