<H3> <TI>   Kyrgyz Soldiers May Keep Peace on Abkhaz-Georgian Border </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kyrgyz Soldiers May Keep Peace on Abkhaz-Georgian Border </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606155994 Moscow Mayak Radio Network in Russian 1230 GMT 
16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606155994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Mayak Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] It is quite probable that in the near future the 
Defense Ministry of Kirghizia [Kyrgyzstan] will embark on the 
formation of another subunit forming part of the CIS peacemaking 
forces. As an RIA correspondent has been informed, it is 
envisaged that Kirghiz servicemen will defend the interests of 
the Commonwealth on the mobile [podvizhnaya] border between 
Georgia and Abkhazia. This was occasioned by the agreement 
between Russia and Georgia on introduction of Russian 
peacemaking forces. 

</TEXT>

