<DATE1>  16 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> CAUCASUS </F>
<F P=101> Armenia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Azerbaijan Accused of Violating International Agreements </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Azerbaijan Accused of Violating International Agreements </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1606151494 Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN in 
English 0626 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1606151494 </F>
<F P=104>  Yerevan ARAGIL ELECTRONIC NEWS BULLETIN </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Stepanakert ("LRAGIR" daily), 06/16/94 -- The RMK 
[Republic of Mountainous Karabakh] military experts believe, 
despite several defeats in winter and spring, Azerbaijan still 
has a significant attack potential, and keeps expansive 
intentions. 
  Attempting to defeat the RMK at any price, Azerbaijan 
violates the international agreements it has signed. 
Particularly, based on the agreement on normal [conventional] 
armaments in Europe, this country was only allowed to have 220 
tanks. Nevertheless, according to the RMK military 
reconnaissance, the Azeri army has long exceeded the allowed 
limits. In parallel with this, based on Aliyev's special order, 
a number of large enterprises in Azerbaijan are producing and 
modernizing weaponry. 
  "All these alarming military preparations, as well as fast 
militarization of the economy are originating from the 
all-Turkish idea of creating a Great Azerbaijan," declared 
Deputy Commander in Chief of the RMK defense army Murad 
Petrosyan. "This country has territorial claims to, in fact, 
all neighboring countries and particularly for the Bolnisi and 
Marneuli districts of Georgia, southern districts of Dagestan, 
northern regions of Iran and Zangezur district of Armenia. The 
RMK has become the first target of the Azeri hegemonists, who 
receive military-political support of Turkey". 
  On Petrosyan's opinion not only the future of the RMK 
people, 
but fortunes of a number of countries in Close East and 
Transcaucasia depend on the results of the Karabakh-Azerbaijan 
war. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

