<F P=100> Azerbaijan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Armenian Offer for Border Security, Trade Rejected </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Armenian Offer for Border Security, Trade Rejected </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1606193194 Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network in Azeri 1600 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1606193194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baku Azerbaycan Radio Televiziyasi Television 
Network </F>

<F P=105>  Azeri </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A meeting took place on Sadarak Rayon's border on 14 
June between Namik Gasanov, chairman of Nakhichevan Autonomous 
Republic Supreme Mejlis, and two representatives of the Armenian 
Republic: Shakhnazaryan, the Armenian president's 
plenipotentiary representative; and Arutyunyan, chief border 
guards commissar. An agreement was reached during the 
two-hour-long meeting to maintain peace on the border. 
  It is being stated in connection with the Armenian side's 
proposal to open a joint trade center on the border that this is 
not possible between countries at war and when a part of our 
territory is under occupation. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

