<H3> <TI>   Supreme Council Chairman Moroz Leaves for Simferopol </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Supreme Council Chairman Moroz Leaves for Simferopol </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606141694 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1130 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606141694 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 16 June -- Ukraine's Supreme Council chairman 
has left for Simferopol. Mr. Moroz told UNIAN that the main 
purpose of his visit was to meet Crimean Supreme Council 
deputies. "The Crimean authorities' alienation from the center 
does not contribute to the settlement of Crimean problems," said 
the Supreme Council chairman. Considering the frequent bias in 
some of the media coverage of the Crimean issues as well as 
third party political manipulations "by Russia," Oleksandr Moroz 
plans personal meetings with Crimea's residents and labor 
collectives in person. There will be no time for a meeting with 
the Black Sea Fleet command, although the Ukrainian Supreme 
Council chairman said he was willing to hold one. 

</TEXT>

