<F P=100> National Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Admits Kiev Errors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Admits Kiev Errors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606165794 Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service in Ukrainian 
1600 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606165794 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev Radio Ukraine World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] We arrived here to fill the gap between the 
authorities of Kiev and Crimea, said Oleksandr Moroz, Supreme 
Council chairman of Ukraine, while speaking in the Crimean 
Supreme Council today. Our task, he pointed out, is to establish 
business and emotional contacts. However, we have prospects 
only on condition that we work in a single constitutional field, 
said Oleksandr Moroz. 
  According to the Ukrainian Supreme Council speaker, the 
aggravation of the situation in Crimea was caused not only by 
the local authorities' actions, but also by the mistakes made by 
the Kiev authorities. 
  Touching on the Black Sea Fleet issue, Oleksandr Moroz 
pointed out that this is a zone of special interest of Ukraine 
and Russia. In the opinion of Oleksandr Moroz, the Black Sea 
Fleet should be used jointly by both countries and it should 
have a joint command. However, the Supreme Council chairman 
pointed out, Ukraine and Russia should maintain and be in charge 
of their own parts of the fleet. 
  Oleksandr Moroz held a news conference for journalists 
during 
which he, in particular, spoke out against the federal system in 
Ukraine, saying that the time has not yet come for this. 

</TEXT>

