<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk: Sevastopol Cannot Be Base of Russian Navy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk: Sevastopol Cannot Be Base of Russian Navy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606190294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1821 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606190294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondents Viktor Demidenko and </F>
Mikhail Melnik] 
  [Text] Odessa 16 June TASS -- "Ukraine is ready to consider 
the problems of the Black Sea navy by taking interests of the 
Russian Federation into account, but the Russian Federation 
should take into account Ukraine's interests, too," President 
Leonid Kravchuk of Ukraine told servicemen of Ukraine's First 
Aeromobile Division stationed in the Bolgrad district. 
  "The Russian Federation now admits that Crimea is a 
constituent part of Ukraine. We are quite satisfied with this 
approach. However, Ukraine should play a leading part in solving 
the problems of the Black Sea Navy," Kravchuk said. 
  Touching upon differences between Russian and Ukrainian 
approaches to these problems, Kravchuk pointed out that Ukraine 
cannot accept the formulation which Russia wants to force upon 
it, namely that Sevastopol is a base of the Russian Navy. 
  "Sevastopol cannot be a base of the Russian Navy," he said. 
Ukraine proposes another formulation: "A base of the Russian 
Navy in Sevastopol" rather than "the Sevastopol base of the 
Russian Navy." 
  "The whole thing should be adopted in accordance with 
international principles and agreements. Naturally, it may be a 
matter of other bases of our country, too, where ships of 
Russian and Ukrainian Navies may be placed," Kravchuk added. 
  When in the division's quarters, Kravchuk familiarized 
himself with the servicemen's combat readiness, their way of 
life and watched them taking part in demonstration exercises. 
  Kravchuk will leave Izmail for Odessa late at night. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-40521 </DOCNO>
