<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Ministry on Delay in Russian Deployment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Ministry on Delay in Russian Deployment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606204794 Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY in Russian 
1600 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606204794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tbilisi CONTACT INFORMATION AGENCY </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Georgian Defense Ministry press service has 
circulated a report stating that, in accordance with a plan 
agreed upon at the Abkhaz-Georgian Moscow negotiations, the 
deployment of Russian troops in the conflict zone was intended 
to begin on 17 June and be completed on 19 June. 
  However, because of curt statements made by some 
representatives of the parliamentary opposition, urging that the 
implementation of the mission by a Russian peacekeeping 
contingent should not take place, the stationing of troops in 
the conflict zone may presumably be postponed for an indefinite 
period. 

</TEXT>

