<F P=100> Georgia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Batumi Hosts Joint Russo-Georgian Military Course </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Batumi Hosts Joint Russo-Georgian Military Course </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1606153394 Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA in Russian 16 Jun n 94 p 
1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1606153394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow KRASNAYA ZVEZDA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Lieutenant Colonel Sergey Prangishvili and </F>
Captain Vitaliy Denisov: "Joint Studies for Russian and 
Georgian Military"] 
  [Text] A course for commanders and deputy commanders of 
combined and other units began on 15 June at the Batumi garrison 
under the direction of Colonel General Fedor Reut, commander of 
the Group of Russian Forces in the Transcaucasus. A delegation 
from the Georgian Defense Ministry headed by Brigadier General 
Guram Nikolaishvili, first deputy defense minister, is attending 
the course. 
  In conversation with your KRASNAYA ZVEZDA correspondent, Gen 
Guram Niklaishvili stated: "Our contacts with the Russian 
military-political leadership and the command of the Russian 
troops in the Transcaucasus are being strengthened constantly. 
The present event is by no means the first in a series of 
theoretical and practical courses based on the Group of Russian 
Forces in the Transcaucasus that our generals and other officers 
have taken part in." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

