<F P=100> BALTIC STATES </F>
<F P=101> Estonia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Accord Signed With Iceland To Prevent Double Taxation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Accord Signed With Iceland To Prevent Double Taxation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1706075494 Tallinn BNS in English 1804 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1706075494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tallinn, June 16, BNS -- Estonian Ambassador to 
Iceland Arvo Jurgen Alas and Iceland's Foreign Minister Jon 
Baldvin Hannibalsson on Thursday signed in Reykjavik an 
Estonian-Icelandic agreement on avoiding double taxation, the 
Foreign Ministry press service told BNS. 
  After the signing Alas and Hannibalsson discussed Estonian- 
Russian relations, including the problems related to the 
withdrawal of Russian troops from Estonia, and prospects for 
developing economic cooperation between the two countries. 
  The meeting also touched on Iceland's bid to join the 
Council 
of Baltic Sea States, the Foreign Ministry press service informs. 

</TEXT>

