<F P=100> Latvia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Parliament Amends Copyright Stipulations in Radio, TV Law </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Parliament Amends Copyright Stipulations in Radio, TV Law </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   WS1706081394 Tallinn BNS in English 1501 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> WS1706081394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tallinn BNS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Riga, Jun 16, BNS -- The Latvian Saeima 
(parliament) adopted amendments Thursday to the law on radio and 
television stipulating free distribution and use of state-owned 
radio and television program charts. 
  Consequently, legislators rejected the previous version of 
the bill that applied copyright norms to state-owned radio and 
TV programs. 
  Democratic Party's Ilga Grava supported the new version 
claiming that a broadcast schedule is not creative work but "a 
showing of work content of state institutions." 
  The paid publication of the programs would soar newspaper 
prices and tax-payers would have to make additional investment 
into the maintenance of state-owned radio and television, 
speakers said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

