<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Yeltsin Directive on Legislative Process Backup </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yeltsin Directive on Legislative Process Backup </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1606131994 Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA in Russian 16 Jun 94 
First Edition p 4 </F>

<F P=103> PM1606131994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ROSSIYSKAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Russian Federation President's Directive No. 279-rp] </F>
  [Text] With a view to creating the necessary conditions 
for information analysis backup for the legislative process: 
  1. There shall be support for the proposal of the chairmen 
of the Federal Assembly chambers on the transfer of functions to 
do with the management of the Russian Federation parliamentary 
center to the Federal Assembly chambers. 
  2. The Russian Federation president's administration of 
affairs shall: 
  --implement within the established procedure financial and 
material and technical backup for the activity of the Russian 
Federation parliamentary center and also socioconsumer services 
for its workers; 
  --ensure, in accordance with existing legislation, the 
payment of wages and other payments to workers of the Russian 
Federation parliamentary center for the period from 13 December 
1993 through the moment the functions to do with the management 
of the parliamentary center are transferred to the Federal 
Assembly chambers. 
  3. The Russian Federation parliamentary center shall be 
accommodated in Moscow, at number 2 Tsvetnyy Boulevard. 
  [signed] Russian Federation President B. Yeltsin, 6 June 
1994. 

</TEXT>

