<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russia Suspends Flights To Chechnya </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russia Suspends Flights To Chechnya </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606175494 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1712 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606175494 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow June 16 TASS -- Russia has abolished air 
communications with its break-away southern republic of 
Chechnya. The Russian Ministry of Transport has sent a message 
to Groznyy that it suspends all flights from Russian airports to 
Chechnya as well as those from the Chechen capital to any 
airport of Russia, Shirvani Pashayev, an aide of the Chechen 
information minister, told ITAR- TASS by telephone on Thursday. 
  Pashayev said that the flights were suspended under a 
pretext 
that Chechnya gives no guarantees of safety in the air space 
over Groznyy. 

</TEXT>

