<F P=100> UKRAINE </F>
<F P=101> International Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kravchuk Cited on Friendly Relations With Israel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kravchuk Cited on Friendly Relations With Israel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606111594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 0730 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kiev UNIAR </F>
<F P=105>  Ukrainian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Kiev, 15 Jun -- Ukrainian President Leonid Kravchuk 
received Israel's Foreign Minister Shimon Peres during the 
minister's visit to Ukraine. 
  "Ukraine attaches great importance to the development of 
friendly bilateral relations with Israel," the Ukrainian 
president stressed. "This visit opens a new stage in Ukraine's 
relations with Israel." 
  Leonid Kravchuk spoke warmly about his visit to Israel in 
January last year when he signed a memorandum on mutual 
understanding and fundamental principles of cooperation between 
the two countries. At the same time, Ukraine's and Israel's 
foreign ministries signed a protocol on consultations. The two 
countries also signed intergovernmental agreements on 
cooperation in education, culture, science and technology, 
agriculture, and air transportation. 
  "To us, Israel is and has been a sovereign state with which 
we are keen to develop relations," the Ukrainian president said. 
"We are neighbors, and many of our countrymen are now citizens 
of Israel. They live there and they wish Ukraine to be happy. 
  "We have worked out a considerable legislative basis for the 
development of our relations. The main thing is that the people 
of Ukraine want to have friendly relations with Israel, and 
there are no problems that we cannot solve." 

</TEXT>

