<H3> <TI>   World Bank Grants $320 Million for Agriculture </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    World Bank Grants $320 Million for Agriculture </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706020094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 0005 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706020094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Igor Borisenko] </F>
  [Text] Washington, 17 June -- On Thursday the World Bank 
approved the granting of two loans to the Russian Federation for 
the development of agriculture. 
  One of them -- for $240 million -- is intended for 
accelerating the process of reforms in the agricultural sector, 
for creating a network of information and consultation services 
for farmers, for help in organizing individual, highly efficient 
enterprises. The other -- for 80 million dollars -- should 
assist in the process of land reform and privatization. 
  The loans are being granted on what are customary conditions 
for the World Bank, the repayment term is 17 years. 

</TEXT>

