<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Views Proposals on Sanctions Against DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Views Proposals on Sanctions Against DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606170294 Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy in Russian 
1500 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Radiostantsiya Ekho Moskvy </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Valentin Moyiseyev, a top official of the Russian 
Foreign Minsitry working with North Korea, has this to say about 
Russia's proposals regarding the UN Security Council's draft 
resolution on North Korea. 
  [Begin Moyiseyev recording] We believe the draft resolution 
-- and this does not necessary have to be a joint resolution, it 
could be an agreed resolution -- should first consider inviting 
Pyongyang -- not just Pyongyang alone but other countries 
mentioned in our proposal -- for an international conference 
aimed at finding a solution to the problems of the Korean 
peninsula as a whole. And if this conference fails to achieve 
any positive results and after all other political methods of 
solving the Korean nuclear problem are tried and failed, only 
then can step-by-step sanctions be applied. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

