<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Speaker Favors International Forum on DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606160794 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1353 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606160794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Duma Speaker Ivan Rybkin spoke out in favor of 
Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev's call for a conference 
on the Korean peninsula. 
  Talking to journalists in Bonn on Thursday, he said that 
even 
if sanctions were imposed on North Korea, they should be 
implemented in stages. In his opinion, sanctions could be 
applied only after stern warnings. 
  Meanwhile, the head of the Duma's International Affairs 
Committee Vladimir Lukin said that the lower house expects 
Kozyrev to report on the situation in North Korea on Friday. 
And on June 20, the committee will hear from the ambassadors of 
the countries concerned. 

</TEXT>

