<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Calls For Further CIS Integration </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Calls For Further CIS Integration </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606140094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1325 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606140094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Yuriy Kozlov and </F>
Boris Krivoshey] 
  [Text] Moscow June 16 TASS -- Russia should remain the 
"locomotive of reform", and the stronger the Russian state will 
be politically and economically, the better it will be for the 
other CIS countries and integration, according to Russian 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev. 
  Speaking at a Foreign Policy Council meeting devoted to 
further integration in the Commonwealth of Independent States, 
Kozyrev noted that Russia is also interested in the all-round 
strengthening of the CIS member-countries, so that she would be 
surrounded by stable states. He said Russia was ready for as 
much integration as its partners desired. 
  Kozyrev pointed out that there are a lot of far-reaching 
ideas being bandied about now, such as Kazakhstan President 
Nursultan Nazarbayev's proposal to create a Euroasian Union, or 
ideas about forming a confederation. 
  From Russia's point of view, any of these proposals would be 
acceptable. However, "it would be best to avoid a situation in 
which the proposal and discussion of such promising ideas does 
not hinder us in solving specific pressing problems, or distract 
our attention from them", Kozyrev said. He stated that it was 
most important to concentrate joint efforts on coordinating 
legislative activity and searching for ways to make the CIS 
interparliamentary assembly more effective. 
  The Foreign Policy Council's meeting was attended by 
representatives from the parliament, various ministeries and 
departments, political and public organisations, and the clergy. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

