<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Contact Group on Bosnia-Herzegovina Meets in London </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Contact Group on Bosnia-Herzegovina Meets in London </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606150194 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1453 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606150194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vladimir Voronkov] </F>
  [Text] London June 16 TASS -- The "contact group", 
comprising Russia, the United States and the European Union is 
holding a working session in the British capital today in its 
bid to work out a peaceful solution to the crisis in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina and its future constitutional and territorial 
set up. Russian presidential special envoy and Deputy Foreign 
Minister Vitaliy Churkin is taking part in the meeting. 
  The British Foreign Office told ITAR-TASS that all parties 
at 
the session are striving to agree to the last details of the 
"geographical division" map of the Former Republic of 
Yugoslavia. The whole package is to be approved at a 
minister-level meeting of Russia, the U.S., Great Britain, 
France and Germany, which is scheduled to take place within the 
next two to three weeks. 
  Later the documents, which are in informed circles regarded 
as ultimatums of their own kind, will be handed over to the 
Serbs, Croats and Moslems, the hostile sides in 
Bosnia-Herzegovina. The range of the issues discussed by the 
"contact group" is extremely complicate, the British Foreign 
Office representative noted. For this reason, the possibility 
of the talks being extended until friday cannot be ruled out, he 
indicated. 
  According to British Foreign Secretary Douglas Hurd, the 
international committee has only a few days left at its disposal 
to put an end to the Bosnian conflict. Speaking in London on 
Wednesday, Hurd noted that there exists a real danger of a new 
war braking out in Bosnia-Herzegovina, which may spill over 
beyond its borders. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

