<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev on Dialogue With Baltic States </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev on Dialogue With Baltic States </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606151994 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1427 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606151994 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Yuriy Kozlov and </F>
Boris Krivoshey] 
  Moscow June 16 TASS -- Russia is trying to maintain 
friendly relations with not only the CIS country-members, but 
with the Baltic countries as well, according to Russian Foreign 
Minister Andrey Kozyrev. 
  Kozyrev, speaking at a foreign policy council meeting on 
Thursday, said civilised dialogue was being strengthened between 
Russia and the three Baltic states. The questions of human 
rights violations and the rights of the Russian-language 
population and other minorities in the Baltic region are still 
on the agenda, he said. The Russian foreign minister noted that 
the complete withdrawal of Russian troops from the Baltic 
countries would not lead to a decrease in attention paid to 
those questions. 

</TEXT>

