<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   State Duma Chairman Meets Correspondents in Bonn </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    State Duma Chairman Meets Correspondents in Bonn </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606210894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 2049 GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1606210894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Pavel Kuznestov, Gennadiy </F>
Kulbitskiy, Gennadiy Temnenkov] 
  [Text] Bonn June 16 TASS -- Chairman of the Russian State 
Duma Ivan Rybkin who is on an official visit to Germany as the 
head of a delegation of the lower house of the Russian 
parliament, met with journalists in Bonn on Thursday. 
  "We have agreed with our German colleagues to develop close 
contacts between committees of the State Duma and the German 
Bundestag which deal with economic issues. I believe that 
Bundestag's experience in this field will be of great interest 
for us, especially in matters concerning the economic boost on 
Germany's eastern lands," Rybkin said. 
  He pointed out that during his talks with German leaders on 
Thursday the sides touched upon problems faced by Germans 
residing in Russia and Russians in Germany. "We must do our 
best so that hundreds of thousands of these people could feel at 
home both in Russia and in Germany," Rybkin said. 
  Touching upon problems existing in Russo-German relations, 
Rybkin singled out the problem of mutual return of cultural 
values, removed from Russia and Germany as a result of the 
Second World War, as the most difficult one. 
  Asked about the interaction between the Russian president 
and 
the State Duma and the extent to which the lower house of the 
Russian parliament supports the course of reforms pursued by 
Boris Yeltsin, Rybkin said that "from the very first days of our 
existence we have been acting together with the president and 
shall continue to do so in future to find a way out of the 
quagmire of the crisis". 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

