<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meets With Germany's Weizsaecker </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1606221094 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1122 
GMT 16 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1606221094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS special correspondents Pavel Kuznetsov, </F>
Gennadiy Kulbitskiy, and Gennadiy Temnenkov] 
  [Text] Bonn, 16 Jun -- After a meeting with the head of the 
German state, Ivan Rybkin, chairman of the State Duma, described 
German President Richard von Weizsaecker as "a major state 
figure to whose lot it fell to head Germany during the period of 
the reunification of its eastern and western lands." 
  Replying to a question from an ITAR-TASS correspondent, the 
speaker of the lower chamber of the Federal Assembly said that 
during the talks a wide range of political and economic issues 
connected with relations between the two countries were touched 
upon. 
  Rybkin said Weizsaecker showed great interest in the coming 
into being of the State Duma. In addition, they discussed in 
detail the economic processes that are under way in the Russian 
Federation and also the situation in the agro-industrial 
complex. 

