<H3> <TI>   IL-76 Transports Leave for Africa To Aid Rwandan Refugees </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    IL-76 Transports Leave for Africa To Aid Rwandan Refugees </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706084694 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0826 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706084694 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Anatoliy Yurkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 17 TASS -- Two heavy transport planes 
IL-76 of the Russian Ministry for Emergencies departed from 
Moscow for Tanzania last night, ITAR-TASS learnt at the press 
service of the Ministry for Emergencies on Friday. 
  The cargo is accompanied by a Russian delegation led by 
First 
Deputy Minister for Civil Defence and Emergencies Yuriy Vorobyev. 
  The aim of the visit is a meeting with the Tanzanian 
leadership and the signing of documents on safe flights for 
planes belonging to the ministry. They operate in that country 
from May 20, bringing international humanitarian aid to Rwandan 
refugees. 
  The delegation will also conclude a contract with the agency 
of the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees, under whose aegis 
Russian transport planes operate. 
  Two heavy-duty planes called "Ruslan" will fly to Africa on 
June 20. They will bring another 20 Kamaz lorries to Tanzania. 

</TEXT>

