<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Aleksandr Mineyev] </F>
  [Text] Brussels, 18 June -- Vitaliy Churkin, Russian deputy 
foreign minister, who arrived in Brussels on 17 June, is holding 
talks in NATO Headquarters with Gebhardt von Moltke, the 
alliance's deputy secretary general, an ITAR-TASS correspondent 
has been told at the Russian Embassy. 
  NATO sources said yesterday that the North Atlantic Council 
had entrusted Moltke to meet Russian representatives before 
Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev arrived in Brussels to discuss 
the details of the visit and to finalize the content and title 
of the document that Russia and NATO plan to sign on 22 June, 
when Russia joins the Partnership for Peace program. 

