<H3> <TI>   Moscow Consults U.S., DPRK on Nuclear Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Consults U.S., DPRK on Nuclear Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706190094 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1723 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706190094 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Boris Sitnikov] </F>
  [Text] United Nations June 17 TASS -- Russia is holding 
bilateral consultations with the United States and the DPRK on 
peaceful settlement of the North Korean nuclear problem at the 
United Nations headquarters, Russian Permanent Representative to 
the United Nations Yuliy Vorontsov said here today. 
  "We still want a peaceful solution to this problem, and it 
is 
possible to do it. That is why, we continue to discuss the 
problem at the bilateral level with the United States and North 
Korea. We would like the Security Council to take a decision 
that would help a political solution," said Vorontsov. 

</TEXT>

