<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev on Talks With PRC on Korean Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev on Talks With PRC on Korean Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706192794 Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service in Russian 1725 
GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706192794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS World Service </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondents Dmitiry Gorokhov and </F>
Yuriy Kozlov] 
  [Text] Moscow, 17 Jun -- Qian Qichen, PRC State Council 
vice premier and foreign minister, will within the next few days 
visit the Russian capital. Andrey Kozyrev informed State Duma 
deputies of this on Friday. 
  Asked at what level and with what effectiveness the 
situation 
concerning the Korean Peninsula is being discussed with Beijing, 
the Russian foreign minister said in particular, that there is a 
regular exchange of views. Over the past two years alone the 
head of Russia's foreign policy department "has had five or six 
meetings with the PRC foreign minister, and on each occasion 
this problem was discussed." 
  "Like Russia," A. Kozyrev said, "China is also definitely 
against the DPRK breaking with the nuclear nonproliferation 
regime and in favor of a nuclear-free Korean Peninsula. In 
other words, it favors neither one of the Korean states 
possessing or taking steps to possess nuclear weapons." 
According to the minister "this is the fundamental basis of the 
coincidence and fundamental closeness of the approaches of 
Russia and the PRC." Of course, he went on to say, there are 
nuances of detail and tactics, but in the main the positions of 
the two countries coincide. 

</TEXT>

