<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kozyrev Supports Expanded Conference on DPRK Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kozyrev Supports Expanded Conference on DPRK Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706165294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1637 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706165294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS diplomatic correspondent Dmitriy Gorokhov and </F>
Yuriy Kozlov] 
  [Text] Moscow June 17 TASS -- Russia has expanded its 
formula of the international conference on security and 
non-nuclear status of the Korean peninsula. Moscow thinks that 
the forum can be attended by other interested states, including 
France, Russian Foreign Minister Andrey Kozyrev told State Duma 
deputies here today. 
  "We have suggested the international conference in order to 
discuss the nuclear problem and security on the Korean 
peninsula, do away with any concerns of the DPRK as regards its 
security," said the minister. 
  "We have suggested a conference with a clear number of 
participants. These are, first of all, Russia. It is also the 
United States which concern most of the claims of the DPRK. 
These are China and the neighbouring states of Japan and the 
Republic of Korea. Other states, including France, have shown 
their interest in the conference." 
  In the opinion of Andrey Kozyrev, France can participate in 
the forum "the more so it is a nuclear power and a permanent 
member of the Security Council." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

