<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Says Russia Ready To Boost Cooperation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Says Russia Ready To Boost Cooperation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2006104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1024 GMT 20 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD2006104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondents Aleksey Bukalov and Aleksey </F>
Golyayev] 
  [Text] Milan June 20 TASS -- "Russia and Europe as well as 
Russia and the world have broad prospects for developing diverse 
economic and political cooperation. We cannot go without each 
other," said Russian Premier Viktor Chernomyrdin, speaking at 
the opening ceremony of the 19th World Gas Congress here on 
Monday. 
  The premier stressed that Moscow is waiting for concrete 
proposals from the G7 countries on cooperation in regulating 
investment flows and on development of adequate and specific 
mechanisms for their encouragement and insurance. 
  "Russia wants that the partners in the coming Naples summit 
should recognise it as `a country with a transition economy' and 
made new concrete moves to improve conditions of access of its 
goods to foreign markets," Chernomyrdin said. 
  "I'm sure that the turning of the G7 into a G8 will bring 
about basically important and positive changes in the 
geopolitical balance and create new favourable conditions for 
Russia's full-fledged participation in the world economic 
system." 

</TEXT>

