<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Kondratyev Urges Ratification of Edict on Peacekeeping </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Kondratyev Urges Ratification of Edict on Peacekeeping </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1806153294 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1310 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806153294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Russia's Deputy Defence Minister, Cl.-General 
Grigoriy Kondratyev, has said he hopes that on Tuesday the 
Federation Council will ratify the presidential decree on 
conducting a peace-keeping operation in the Georgian-Abkhaz 
conflict area. 
  According to him, if the upper chamber of Russia's 
parliament 
resolves this issue positively, military aircraft will start 
lifting Russian peace-keepers to the conflict area on Wednesday. 
  There are plans to despatch 5 Russian battalions to the 
conflict zone. The number of "blue helmets" is to total 25 to 
30 hundred men. 
  This week General Kondratyev visited Abkhazia and inspected 
the locality, where the disengagement of the conflicting sides 
is to take place along the River Inguri. "The military have 
already done all they could to ensure success for the proposed 
peace-keeping operation," he told Interfax on Saturday. 

</TEXT>

