<F P=100> RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<H3> <TI>   Delegation Visits Berlin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Delegation Visits Berlin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1906104894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1027 GMT 19 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1906104894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Berlin June 19 TASS -- Today, on the last day of an 
official visit to Germany, a State Duma delegation, led by its 
Chairman Ivan Rybkin, laid a wreath at the memorial to Russian 
liberator soldiers in the Treptow Park, Berlin. 
  After two days of meetings and talks with leaders and 
prominent politicians in Bonn, Russian legislators arrived in 
the German capital on Saturday, where they familiarised 
themselves with the experience of privatization of state 
enterprises in the eastern part of the country, as well as the 
examples of the participation of foreign business people in that 
process. During their visit to the Kvo Kabel plant, which now 
fully belongs to a British firm and supplies half of its output 
to Russia, as well as during their conversation with Berlin 
Burgomaster Eberhard Dipgen members of the delegation got very 
interesting and useful information, Rybkin told ITAR-TASS. 
"There should be 101 ways of privatization of state-owned 
enterprises instead of just one," Rybkin pointed out. He said 
that at present there are some 1,500 industrial enterprises in 
Russia which may go bankrupt. In the opinion of Rybkin, their 
situation calls for a comprehensive approach. 
  The Russian delegation will have a meeting today with heads 
of the Berlin chamber of deputies in the Palace of 
Charlottenburg. The guests will also visit the Reichstag 
building. In the afternoon of the last day of the visit they 
will have meetings with the command of the Western Army group 
and the personnel of the Berlin Brigade. 

</TEXT>

