<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Party Leaders Comment </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Party Leaders Comment </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706184194 Moscow Russian Television Network in Russian 
1600 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1706184194 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow Russian Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Vesti" newscast; passages within quotation marks </F>
recorded] 
  [Text] [Correspondent M. Lillevyali] The State Duma is in 
its own way a microcosm of our society and we went there today 
to put a question to some of the elected representatives: How 
do you feel about the president's edict on new means for 
fighting crime? 
  [Gennadiy Zyuganov, leader of Communist Party of Russia] "I 
take a dual position here. On the one hand, I would support any 
measures aimed at stopping gangsterism. But on the other hand, 
they must be within the law." 
  [Yekaterina Lakhova, leader of Women of Russia faction] "The 
president's edict cannot exceed the Constitution and cannot 
exceed federal law. All those who drafted the edict, and I 
understand that it was the president who drafted the edict, the 
people who drafted the edict, drafted a completely 
unconstitutional edict. I am very concerned by some of the 
individual formulations -- the legislative committee discussed 
them yesterday -- that tally directly with 1937 formulations." 
  [Vladimir Zhirinovskiy, leader of Liberal Democratic Party 
of 
Russia] "They should have added our program. An emergency 
should be introduced in certain regions of the country. In 
certain cases, we should resort to the court martial system and 
throw the Armed Forces into the fight against crime. The 
militia cannot cope. It needs to be given the right to hold 
additional weapons. The right of the citizen to bear arms 
should be defended. That is the only way. It would be 
temporary. The country's leadership introduced such an edict in 
1947. It was very effective." 
  [Grigoriy Yavlinskiy, leader of Yabloko faction] 
"Introducing 
the atmosphere of a free-for-all and giving some people the 
chance to break all sorts of laws in order to tackle other 
criminals will not in any way solve things." 
  [Lillevyali] We would like to finish with the point of view 
of a professional lawyer -- the chairman of the State Duma 
Security Committee, Viktor Ilyukhin. 
  [Ilyukhin] "It is first unconstitutional and contradicts the 
Constitution. Second, it torpedoes the complete judicial system 
now in existence. As a lawyer, I have every reason to question 
the ability of judicial bodies, which have always been guided 
only by the Constitution and only by the law, to implement it. 
What will the reaction of the court be when a sentence is 
passed on the basis of the edict and not the law?" 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

