<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Deputies Protest Suspension of SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Deputies Protest Suspension of SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Suspension Seen as `Political Act' </H4>

<F P=102> PM1706202594 Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA in Russian 
18 Jun 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PM1706202594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow NOVAYA YEZHEDNEVNAYA GAZETA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Own information report: "SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA Prevents </F>
Deputies Working"] 
  [Text] Yet again the Pressa publishing house has been 
forced to suspend publication of SOVETSKAYA ROSSIYA because of 
large debts (there was a similar precedent in the spring). 
  But some deputies have regarded this event as a political 
act. Gennadiy Seleznev, deputy chairman of the State Duma 
Committee for Information Policy and member of the Communist 
faction, described this as "an extremely gross violation of 
readers' rights," after which some deputies refused to register 
for a session of the Duma. 

</TEXT>

