<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Duma Attack on President's Legality Fails </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Duma Attack on President's Legality Fails </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706125794 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1143 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706125794 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 17 TASS -- An attack on Russian 
President Boris Yeltsin has not been supported by the majority 
of deputies in the State Duma. Independent Deputy Nadezhda 
Verveyko of the Krasnodar territory suggested at a plenary 
meeting of the Duma on Friday that an item on the Russian 
president's oath be put on the agenda of the session. She 
asserted that for several months now the Russian president has 
been working without being sworn in. A minority of deputies of 
the State Duma voted for her proposal. 
  Deputy from Russia's Choice group Anatoliy Yushchenko who 
spoke in the debate pointed out that Nadezhda Verveyko, a 
trained jurist, should know that under articles of the new 
Russian Constitution for the transitional period the president 
need not be sworn in a second time. Nevertheless Verveyko has 
insisted on the voting. 
  It is surprising that despite the clarity of the matter she 
was still supported by 178 votes. 

</TEXT>

