<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Credentials Commission To Decide on Zhirinovskiy Case </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Credentials Commission To Decide on Zhirinovskiy Case </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706114894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1107 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706114894 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS parliamentary correspondent Ivan Novikov] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 17 TASS -- The Council of the Russian 
parliament lower house relegated a representation by Russian 
Prosecutor-General Vladimir Ilyushenko on divesting Vladimir 
Zhirinovskiy, leader of the Russian Liberal Democratic Party, of 
a legislator's immunity to the house's credentials commission 
for examination, Valentin Kovalev who chaired the chamber's 
plenary meeting on Friday, said here. 
  It will be remembered that the acting prosecutor-general 
claims in his representation that Zhirinovskiy's book "The Last 
Leap to the South" is liable to criminal prosecution. 
  The report by Kovalev provoked a lively response from 
legislators. For instance, Deputy Andrey Dorovskiy from the 
LDPR group insisted that lawmakers should vote to return the 
representation by Ilyushenko who, in the deputy's opinion, had 
no powers to sign such a document, since he "was not approved as 
prosecutor-general". 
  Another proposal -- to put the item on the representation on 
the session's agenda -- did not pass either: The motion was 
short of 20 votes. 

</TEXT>

