<F P=100> Federal Assembly </F>
<H3> <TI>   Zhirinovskiy Attacks Duma's Decision on Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Zhirinovskiy Attacks Duma's Decision on Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706193594 Moscow INTERFAX in English 1608 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706193594 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow INTERFAX </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Leader of the Liberal Democratic Party of Russia 
(LDPR) Vladimir Zhirinovskiy sharply criticized the decision of 
the State Duma to transfer to the mandate commission the appeal 
of acting Prosecutor General Aleksey Ilyushenko asking for the 
consent of the Duma for bringing Zhirinovskiy to justice on 
warmongering and inciting ethnic hatred charges. 
  Zhirinovskiy stated that Ilyushenko himself was "nobody and 
is sitting in his office only because the president wants it." 
  Ilyushenko motivated his appeal by the results of the 
preliminary investigations due to the publication of 
Zhirinovskiy's book "The Last Push for the South." Ilyushenko 
referred to provisions in the Criminal Code against warmongering 
and inciting ethnic hatred. 

</TEXT>

