<H3> <TI>   St Petersburg Threatened With No Electricity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    St Petersburg Threatened With No Electricity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1706131394 Moscow IZVESTIYA in Russian 16 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> PM1706131394 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow IZVESTIYA </F>
<F P=105>  Russian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Sergey Krayukhin: "Necessary to Do Without </F>
Electricity During White Nights"] 
  [Text] St. Petersburg -- The "Lentransgaz" Production 
Association has delivered a tough ultimatum to the "Lenenergo" 
Joint-Stock Company -- it is threatening to stop supplying gas 
to all St. Petersburg's power stations as of 21 June as a result 
of outstanding debts. 
  The penalty [neustoyka] has reached the immense figure of 60 
billion rubles. While cast in the role of debtor, the 
"Lenenergo" Joint-Stock Company, for its part, cannot obtain the 
money owed to it by its own big customers -- enterprises in the 
former "defense sector." For the people of St. Petersburg the 
result of this clash between the two giants could be that their 
apartments will be lit at the end of June not by electricity, 
but by the dim glow of the white nights. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

