<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Dudayev Accuses Russia of `Political Blackmail' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Dudayev Accuses Russia of `Political Blackmail' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1706132294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1220 GMT 17 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1706132294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Vadim Byrkin] </F>
  [Text] Moscow June 17 TASS -- President of Russia's 
breakaway Chechen Republic Dzhokhar Dudayev accused Russian 
authorities of "political blackmail" after the Russian Transport 
Ministry suspended all regular flights to Chechnya since the 
latter failed to guarantee safety of aircraft over Groznyy. 
  "The action has shown the world community once again that 
the 
Russian leadership does not adhere to any principles, except to 
those of political blackmail and terrorism", Dudayev said. 
  A source in the Chechen Information Ministry told TASS by 
telephone that the action is assessed in the republic as a 
declaration of an air blockade of Chechnya ordered by Russia's 
political leadership. 
  The Chechen Foreign Ministry's statement circulated on 
Friday, qualified the decision to suspend flights as "not 
corresponding to the norms of international law and delivering 
serious damage to the relations between the two countries". 
  The statement suggested the flights to Chechnya be resumed 
and qualified the reference to the alleged lack of flight safety 
as not corresponding to reality. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

