<F P=100> Regional Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   Russian Procurator Ilyushenko Visiting N. Caucasus </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Russian Procurator Ilyushenko Visiting N. Caucasus </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Murder To Be Investigated Further </H4>

<F P=102> LD1806174294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1721 GMT 18 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1806174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By ITAR-TASS correspondent Valeriy Shanayev] </F>
  [Text] Vladikavkaz June 18 TASS -- "Additional 
investigation should be held" in the murder of Viktor 
Polyanichko and his associates, Acting Russian Procurator 
General Aleksey Ilyushenko said here today. 
  Ilyushenko has completed a trip to Northern Ossetia and 
Ingushetia as part of preparations for a Russian Government 
meeting on problems of these republics. 
  He said that "several versions of murder of former head of 
the temporary administration Polyanichko and the accompanying 
officials have been analyzed but not confirmed." 
  The temporary administration head and the accompanying 
military were killed on August 1, 1993, near the Tarskoye 
settlement of the North Ossetian Prigorodnyy region. 
Unidentified persons put under automatic gun fire the car of 
Polyanichko and head of the Vladikavkaz garrison Major-General 
Anatoliy Koretskiy. Both died of wounds on the spot. The fire 
exchange also fatally wounded body guard of the temporary 
administration head Senior Lieutenant Viktor Kravchuk. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

